{"word":"φραγμός","slug":"φραγμός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>φραγμός</b></el> <el>(φραγμός, οῦ, ὁ,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:φράσσω'><el>φράσσω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>a fencing in, blocking up</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>like <el>φράγμα</el>, <i>a fence, paling, palisade</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>a place fenced off, an enclosure</i>, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>a partition</i>, <b><a href='S:New Testament'>NTest.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}